---
// ✅ [FEATURE]: GuideHeader — persistent sticky brand bar for /guides pages (Batch 6, F-19).
// Goes at: src/components/GuideHeader.astro
//
// Problem: a visitor landing on a guide from search has no top-level path back
// to the product — only a small "← All guides" text link. This is deliberately
// NOT used on the homepage (which has its own immersive hero) or on
// privacy/terms — just the guide hub + guide articles, where visitors are
// most likely to arrive cold from search/AI answer engines.
//
// Design: reuses the site's existing forest-deep + white-pill tokens (no new
// colors), sits flush above the guides hub's existing dark header (same
// bg-forest-deep, so at scroll-top they read as one seamless block — the
// slim bar only reveals itself as separate chrome once you scroll past the
// hub's intro banner and it sticks). On guide articles (light background,
// no existing dark band) it reads as clean top-of-page brand chrome, same
// treatment the rest of the site already uses to bookend content (Hero,
// footer). Pure CSS `sticky` — no JS, no hydration, zero bundle cost.
//
// CTA deliberately links to "/" (the full pitch + both store buttons), not
// straight to an app store — guide visitors are research-stage, and skipping
// the "Havyu is the AI Coach" sell step straight to an install prompt is a
// worse funnel than routing through the homepage first.
---

<div class="sticky top-0 z-40 bg-forest-deep">
  <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-5xl items-center justify-between px-6 py-3">
    <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-white/80 rounded-md">
      <img src="/havyu-mark.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" width="360" height="250" class="h-7 w-auto" />
      <span class="font-display text-sm font-bold text-white">Havyu AI</span>
    </a>
    <a
      href="/"
      class="rounded-full bg-white px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-bold text-forest shadow-card transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-white/80"
    >
      Get the app
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
